1
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:39,233
<i>- Jeff!
- Jeffrey!</i>

2
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:40,300
<i> Jeff!</i>

3
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:43,467
<i>Why did you jump
into the pool to save me?</i>

4
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,033
<i>If any of my children
are in danger,</i>

5
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:46,533
<i>I wouldn't hesitate
to save them.</i>

6
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:47,933
<i> Even if it costs me my life.</i>

7
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:49,933
<i>- Sorry.
- You risked your life again.</i>

8
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,433
<i> You saved someone's life.</i>

9
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:55,567
<i>Please save some for yourself,
for me.</i>

10
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,433
<i>That's just how we fathers are.</i>

11
00:00:57,567 --> 00:01:00,467
<i>You're all my blood and flesh.
I won't let anyone get hurt.</i>

12
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,567
<i>Andrea, did you know?
Dad saved Jeff earlier.</i>

13
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:05,067
<i>- Have you reconciled with him?
- Andrea...</i>

14
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:07,833
<i>He betrayed me too, just like
what Mom and Coleen did!</i>

15
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,367
<i>I really hope the annulment with
Hazel finally gets approved.</i>

16
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:11,833
<i> So I can marry you.</i>

17
00:01:11,967 --> 00:01:14,000
<i>- What happens to Jessica?
- She should stay with her mom.</i>

18
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:16,133
<i> She's her real mother anyway.</i>

19
00:01:16,267 --> 00:01:18,300
<i>I don't want her
to be part of our family.</i>

20
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:20,900
<i>I don't want them
to take you away from me, Dad.</i>

21
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:23,333
<i>They will erase you
from your dad's life.</i>

22
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:24,633
<i> So you must act.</i>

23
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:29,233
<i>We must take your dad back
before he learns the truth.</i>

24
00:01:29,367 --> 00:01:30,900
<i> Yes, Mom.</i>

25
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:36,533
Dad, here. Eat plenty of rice.

26
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:37,933
- Son, that's enough.
- One last scoop.

27
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:39,300
That's more than enough.

28
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:41,867
I might get spoiled
if you keep doing that.

29
00:01:42,033 --> 00:01:45,033
I told Coleen
I'd make it up to you.

30
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:47,000
I did you so many wrongs.

31
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,167
Thank you, Dad,

32
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,533
for...

33
00:01:53,667 --> 00:01:56,367
saving me, even though
it could have harmed you.

34
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,267
Son,

35
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,367
any parent would do that
for their child.

36
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,267
You don't owe me anything, okay?

37
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,633
It's my responsibility.

38
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:16,100
I wish I could also do that
to Tetay.

39
00:02:16,267 --> 00:02:18,033
Be responsible for her.

40
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,800
Jeffrey, son.

41
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,600
Don't be sad.

42
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:29,333
You and Tetay will reunite
at the right time.

43
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:33,100
By the way, I'm going to meet...

44
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:34,833
Colonel Sarabia.

45
00:02:34,967 --> 00:02:36,900
He said he knows someone
in the Australian Embassy

46
00:02:37,033 --> 00:02:38,833
whom we can ask for help.

47
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:42,167
There you go, Jeff.

48
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,033
Please cheer up now.

49
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:47,667
And knowing Tetay, she will find
a way to reconnect with you.

50
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:49,467
Let's just wait.

51
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:51,133
Yes, son.

52
00:02:51,267 --> 00:02:53,867
Take, for example,
Jessica and Coleen.

53
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,100
They found a way to talk
to me, even in secret.

54
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:01,867
Mom, Dad, I'm planning
to visit Andrea later.

55
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,267
Okay, son.

56
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:07,367
I'll cook some food
so you can bring it to her.

57
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,700
Say hi to her for me.

58
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:13,133
Tell her she can come home now.

59
00:03:13,267 --> 00:03:15,467
Jessica and I
are leaving anyway.

60
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,600
You're leaving, Dad?

61
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:20,233
We still haven't made it up
to each other.

62
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,600
- Please don't leave.
- What?

63
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:24,500
No! Dad and I are leaving!

64
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:34,033
I mean...

65
00:03:34,167 --> 00:03:36,767
So there won't be
any more trouble with Mom.

66
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,133
She can make trouble
as long as she wants.

67
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:42,500
I'm here to protect my family.

68
00:03:42,633 --> 00:03:44,800
So Dad, do we have a deal?

69
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:47,100
I'll take care of Andrea.
I promise she'll come home.

70
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:52,500
It depends on your mom.

71
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:59,533
Okay, let's discuss it.

72
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:02,233
But let's enjoy
our breakfast first.

73
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:03,633
Go on and eat.

74
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,000
Here's some more.

75
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,267
Yes, I understand.

76
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,467
- Jeffrey, coffee.
- Of course.

77
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,967
Thank you. Thank you.

78
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,533
- You know...
- Of course.

79
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:27,000
She'll eat it.
It's her favorite.

80
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:29,433
This is delicious.

81
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:32,767
Afritada ang adobo.
This is good.

82
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,633
Yes, I'm really sorry.

83
00:04:35,767 --> 00:04:36,733
But...

84
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:40,567
please tell the other
investors in FMP

85
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,667
to just wait a little longer.

86
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,900
Don't worry,
I'll do something.

87
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:47,133
- I'll take care of it.
- Okay.

88
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:48,933
Okay, bye.

89
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:55,100
Coffee?

90
00:04:55,233 --> 00:04:56,533
What is it?

91
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:58,767
Maybe I can help.

92
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,267
Jeff, can you please
stay out of it?

93
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,100
Just go back to your dad.

94
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:03,867
And give me back
the keycard I gave you.

95
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,233
You're not welcome here anymore.

96
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:07,067
Andrea, can we talk calmly?

97
00:05:09,233 --> 00:05:10,233
Jeff, please.

98
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:13,033
I don't have time
for any drama.

99
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:17,833
Andrea, your...

100
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:19,333
phone.

101
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,867
I've memorized your lines.

102
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,267
Is it okay if I take this call?

103
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,633
I know your spiels.
I can do this. Trust me.

104
00:05:27,767 --> 00:05:29,433
Is it okay?

105
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:30,900
Do whatever you want.

106
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,033
Hello?

107
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:53,667
Please let's stop fighting.

108
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,467
I've just told you, Jeff.

109
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,900
I don't care
about whatever that is.

110
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:00,433
Leave me out of it.

111
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:03,400
Andrea.

112
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:06,533
I said I don't care!

113
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:11,033
If you want to reconcile
with your dad, it's your choice.

114
00:06:11,167 --> 00:06:12,533
That's on you.

115
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:14,700
And for the record,

116
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:19,033
if you choose to get closer
to your new sister,

117
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:21,000
I don't care.

118
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:24,467
Do whatever you want.
Go bond with them.

119
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:28,567
Andrea, I went back home because
Daisy and I had a problem.

120
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,100
And Tetay got dragged into it.

121
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:34,133
So you and Daisy
had a problem.

122
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:35,633
Why didn't you come to me?

123
00:06:35,767 --> 00:06:37,600
I could've talked to her.

124
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:39,033
But no.

125
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:41,000
I only heard it from Coleen.

126
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:45,100
You chose to come home
to your father.

127
00:06:45,233 --> 00:06:46,233
So, go.

128
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:48,600
I didn't expect
I'd be in an accident.

129
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,700
And that he would save me.

130
00:07:03,067 --> 00:07:04,933
That's when I realized
he loves me so much

131
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,867
despite my anger.

132
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:12,567
And even if I disrespected
him many times.

133
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:17,500
Why are you telling me that,
Jeff?

134
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:20,267
What do you want?

135
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:22,767
Do you want me to do
what you did?

136
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:25,133
Forgive him and be
okay with everyone?

137
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:30,100
Andrea, our father's waiting
for you.

138
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:32,400
He's waiting for your return.

139
00:07:32,533 --> 00:07:35,800
If only you would give him
a chance...

140
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,600
I'm sure you'll
soften to him, too.

141
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:42,200
Jeff, I've got a lot
of things to fix.

142
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:43,900
Things that are way
more important

143
00:07:44,033 --> 00:07:46,567
than my relationship
with your dad.

144
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,367
So please, Jeff.

145
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:49,933
Just go.

146
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:52,400
You're just wasting
your time here.

147
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:12,033
Always remember

148
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,800
that we're here.

149
00:08:13,933 --> 00:08:15,267
You have a family...

150
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,900
waiting for your return.

151
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:28,267
Eat that Afritada.

152
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:44,167
Miss Andrea mentioned it
and asked us...

153
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:47,700
not to tell you about this.

154
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,833
But...

155
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:52,467
it has become a big problem.

156
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,833
We can't solve it ourselves.

157
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:00,433
What problem
do you have with Andrea?

158
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:06,133
Miss Andrea recruited us
to invest in a lending company

159
00:09:06,267 --> 00:09:10,333
owned by her high school
batchmate, Miss Elvie.

160
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:13,033
Now, we can't contact
Miss Elvie anymore.

161
00:09:13,167 --> 00:09:17,167
Even Ma'am Andrea herself
disappeared, too.

162
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:19,467
- We've been scammed, Ma'am.
- Oh, no...

163
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,267
We're in big trouble.

164
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:24,033
Sis, Mayette invested, too!

165
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,933
How much money
are we talking here?

166
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:31,267
Each of us...

167
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:34,333
put in 50,000 pesos.

168
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:38,367
And for most of us,
it was our life savings.

169
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,333
Ma'am...

170
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:45,133
please, help us.

171
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,933
I'll talk to Andrea.

172
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:57,200
We'll help you get
your money back.

173
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:03,500
Thank you Ma'am.

174
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,333
They said
in our college group chat

175
00:10:20,467 --> 00:10:22,633
that Elvie left the country.

176
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:25,833
She took all the
investors' money with her.

177
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,000
Even mine.

178
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:33,500
They said her lending
company's office is shut down.

179
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:37,133
Many people still haven't
received their earnings.

180
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,733
Joel, what am I supposed to do?

181
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:45,567
So many people joined
because of me.

182
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:49,500
I feel so sorry for them,
all their money...

183
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,400
Now I'm getting bashed online.

184
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:55,167
They're calling me a scammer.

185
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:58,267
Why don't you help them
understand that people...

186
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:02,233
like you just wanted
to grow their money, too?

187
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:04,000
That's why
you got into investing.

188
00:11:04,133 --> 00:11:06,300
I already told them that, Joel.

189
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,067
But that's not what they see.

190
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,400
All they see is a scammer.

191
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:13,300
That it was my fault.

192
00:11:13,433 --> 00:11:15,100
That I was in on it.

193
00:11:16,167 --> 00:11:18,833
Even though
we're all victims here.

194
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:20,200
Andrea,

195
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:22,067
we all make mistakes.

196
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:25,400
I need to find Elvie.

197
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:27,900
I have to track her down.

198
00:11:28,033 --> 00:11:30,600
I'll get back
all the investors' money.

199
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:33,400
I'll recover mine
and return it to them.

200
00:11:36,133 --> 00:11:37,900
I was so stupid, Joel.

201
00:11:39,767 --> 00:11:43,667
So stupid to believe Elvie.
To trust her.

202
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:45,600
And I dragged other
people into this.

203
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:49,767
What do I do now?

204
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:10,033
Remember what
you told me before?

205
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:12,867
To enjoy the time
I had left with Dad?

206
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,467
Now...

207
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,767
it feels like I should
be the one saying that to you.

208
00:12:23,733 --> 00:12:25,167
Wait a minute.

209
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:27,933
Why are you so eager
to leave with Dad now, huh?

210
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:31,100
So you can have him
all to yourself?

211
00:12:31,233 --> 00:12:32,867
Keep dreaming!

212
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:38,267
Are you expecting someone?

213
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,100
No, unless Jeff came back.

214
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:42,667
- I'll get the door.
- Come on. I got it.

215
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,400
He won't stop.
He's even adding to the mess.

216
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,633
Come in.

217
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,433
Sonny?

218
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:53,267
Where's Elvie?

219
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,600
Where is she?

220
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:56,033
Where's your accomplice?

221
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:58,033
Give me back my money.
Where is it?

222
00:12:58,167 --> 00:12:59,433
I don't know either, Sonny.

223
00:12:59,567 --> 00:13:01,267
I swear, I don't know anything.

224
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,133
Don't fool me! I know you were
in on it with her!

225
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:04,100
Hey. Bro, hold on.

226
00:13:04,233 --> 00:13:05,667
Chill out.

227
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,767
You're too worked up.
You're talking to a woman.

228
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:11,100
Maybe we can settle this calmly.

229
00:13:13,033 --> 00:13:14,800
Let go of me, Coleen.

230
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:19,067
You know what?

231
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,900
If you like to leave,

232
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,800
go ahead.

233
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:25,267
Or better yet,
go back to your mom.

234
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:28,967
But you're not taking my dad
with you.

235
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:31,467
He stays with us.

236
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,200
With us.

237
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:35,300
- Get out of my way! Move!
- Hey, wait.

238
00:13:35,433 --> 00:13:36,833
Calm down.

239
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,667
Stop! That's enough! Stop!

240
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,600
Stop it, please! Stop.

241
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:46,000
Stop.

242
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:49,533
That's enough, Joel.

243
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:50,767
Stop!

244
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:54,167
Stop.

245
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,033
Stop it!

246
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,233
That's enough.

247
00:13:58,367 --> 00:14:01,800
You will never take my
father away from me, Coleen.

248
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:04,067
I won't allow it.

249
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,667
I regret ever letting you in!

250
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:27,833
You're stealing my dad! Stealer!

251
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,600
Same here, Coleen!

252
00:14:29,733 --> 00:14:32,000
I regret ever meeting you!

253
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:32,867
- You're fake!
- Coleen!

254
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,367
You're just
pretending to be nice!

255
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,900
Jessica, that's enough!

256
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,800
Coleen, I said stop!

257
00:14:39,933 --> 00:14:41,033
Jessica!

258
00:14:41,167 --> 00:14:41,933
Jessica!

259
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:43,367
You're just
pretending to be nice!

260
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,233
- Stop it, Jessica!
- Get out of here!

261
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:47,100
- Go on and leave!
- Stop it.

262
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:49,800
You don't belong here!

263
00:14:50,867 --> 00:14:53,200
Stay away from my sister!

264
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:54,300
Jeff,

265
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:56,233
don't make things worse
between your siblings!

266
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:58,533
I didn't start it, Dad!

267
00:14:58,667 --> 00:14:59,967
It was Coleen!

268
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,867
I just defended myself!

269
00:15:03,033 --> 00:15:05,100
Jessica, we saw what happened.

270
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:06,933
You were the first
to get physical.

271
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:12,500
Dad, don't you believe me?

272
00:15:12,633 --> 00:15:13,967
Okay, okay, that's enough.

273
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,300
Make peace, please!

274
00:15:15,433 --> 00:15:17,733
I don't want you two
fighting anymore!

275
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:19,733
No, Dad! No!

276
00:15:22,067 --> 00:15:23,700
Jessica!

277
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:25,100
Jessica!

278
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:27,833
Jessica, come back!

279
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,233
I'm sorry.

280
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:42,467
You got dragged into this.
I really am sorry.

281
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,733
I can't just do nothing.

282
00:15:44,867 --> 00:15:46,133
And don't worry,

283
00:15:46,267 --> 00:15:47,700
I already told the guards to ban
that Sonny guy.

284
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:49,600
He won't be able
to come back here again.

285
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:51,767
You're hurt. Are you sure...

286
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,633
you're okay? Was there no...

287
00:15:54,767 --> 00:15:56,567
- I mean, it might bruise.
- It's fine, really.

288
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:58,967
Don't worry about it.

289
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:00,867
What about you?
What are you planning to do?

290
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:08,133
You know...

291
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,100
it doesn't feel safe
for you here anymore.

292
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:13,567
What?

293
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,267
Where am I supposed to go?

294
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:21,133
You want me to hide?

295
00:16:21,267 --> 00:16:23,867
That would just make it
look like I'm guilty.

296
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:26,500
No.

297
00:16:26,633 --> 00:16:29,667
I won't be like Elvie,
running away from our investors.

298
00:16:32,133 --> 00:16:33,833
I'll find a way.

299
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:37,833
I'll make sure
they get their money back.

300
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:39,567
Don't worry, Andrea.

301
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:41,267
I'm staying right here.

302
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,800
I'll help you.

303
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:47,733
Thank you.

304
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:51,900
Come on.

305
00:16:52,033 --> 00:16:54,567
At least put some ice on it,
please.

306
00:17:02,133 --> 00:17:04,100
How's Coleen?

307
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:06,200
Still crying.

308
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:08,433
I'll check on her again later.

309
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:10,300
What about...

310
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:12,967
Jessica?

311
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:15,600
Didang and I
didn't catch up to her.

312
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:17,567
Maybe she went
to her mom's place.

313
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:22,500
Sorry, Dad,

314
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:24,367
for yelling at her earlier.

315
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:32,133
What's this?
Why am I tagged in this?

316
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,900
Andrea's involved
in a lending investment scam?

317
00:17:40,033 --> 00:17:41,633
What?

318
00:17:41,767 --> 00:17:43,800
Hold on.

319
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:45,233
Oh my god.

320
00:17:49,867 --> 00:17:51,233
She's not answering.

321
00:17:53,767 --> 00:17:56,867
Sir Manuel, Jeffrey...

322
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,667
I just read it
in our group chat.

323
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:05,200
They said Andrea's involved
in an investment scam.

324
00:18:06,233 --> 00:18:07,167
My god.

325
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:13,433
Isn't Elvie Uy's lending
company popular?

326
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:15,600
She apparently recruited
a lot of people.

327
00:18:15,733 --> 00:18:16,967
Oh my god.

328
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:20,300
Poor Andeng. She needs help.

329
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:21,433
But how?

330
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:28,800
Oh no. No one knows
where Elvie Uy is anymore.

331
00:18:28,933 --> 00:18:33,700
People might go after Andrea
and the others who got involved.

332
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:37,533
I'm scared Andrea
might get mobbed.

333
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:39,467
Here, Sir, look at this.

334
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,667
Hello, Joel, bro...

335
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,467
What's that going around
on FriendsBook about Andrea?

336
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,667
Jeffrey, I was about
to call you.

337
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:47,133
Andrea's in trouble,
but she's innocent.

338
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:48,633
She got scammed, too.

339
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:50,967
Three women stormed
into the condo earlier.

340
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:53,800
They're downstairs, making
a scene, looking for Andrea.

341
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:55,100
What?

342
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:56,467
Joel, what are we going to do?

343
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,300
I'll take care of you.

344
00:18:58,433 --> 00:19:00,033
Joel, what's the plan?
What are you two going to do?

345
00:19:00,167 --> 00:19:02,267
Joel. Joel!

346
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:15,233
Hold on!

347
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,333
Who is it?

348
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:19,600
Wait.

349
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:25,667
Jessica?

350
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,167
Dear.

351
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:31,100
What are you doing here?

352
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:35,000
What's this?

353
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:41,300
Did they hurt you?

354
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:43,400
They're monsters.

355
00:19:57,667 --> 00:19:59,300
Come on. Hurry!

356
00:20:04,633 --> 00:20:05,633
Get in, get in.

357
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,967
Duck down, duck down.

358
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,800
- Joel.
- Wait a second.

359
00:20:16,367 --> 00:20:18,767
- Andrea, hide here.
- Joel, thank you.

360
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,567
I'm sorry you got
dragged into all this.

361
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:22,367
- I didn't know what to do.
- We'll talk later.

362
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:23,433
We have to leave now. Go on.

363
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:25,333
Go on. Hide.

364
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,367
Are you okay there?

365
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:02,200
Sis, do you think Andeng
won't take this the wrong way?

366
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:07,433
I hope not.

367
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,800
But even if she does,
that's fine with me.

368
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:12,867
As long as I can pay off
the people after her.

369
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,567
I don't want her
to be called a scammer.

370
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:22,467
Hey! You little forest spirit!
What are you doing here?

371
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,233
How'd you even get
past the guard?

372
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:25,500
You used black magic,
didn't you?

373
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:26,867
Hey, tree giant!

374
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,533
It's not my fault your guard
fell for my daughter's charm!

375
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:32,300
You've got some nerve.

376
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:35,533
You really used your daughter
for your own selfish gain, huh?

377
00:21:35,667 --> 00:21:37,267
Well, this isn't about me.

378
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,800
It's about my daughter

379
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:42,167
and that war freak daughter
of your best friend!

380
00:21:42,333 --> 00:21:44,533
What are you even
talking about, Hazel?

381
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:47,333
What's your problem this time?

382
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:49,267
Why don't you tell her, Jessica?

383
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,700
Go on. Tell her.

384
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:52,067
Mom, please, let's just go.

385
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:52,900
I can't do this.

386
00:21:53,033 --> 00:21:54,200
- Mom, let's go home!
- Jessica!

387
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:55,900
- Mom, Mom, let's go home!
- We're already here!

388
00:21:56,033 --> 00:21:57,667
- Don't hurt her!
- No, just say it!

389
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,067
- I can't.
- Just say it!

390
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,933
- Stop being so dramatic!
- Don't hurt her!

391
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:02,700
- Hey, Felma!
- Jessica, say it.

392
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:05,800
- So your mom will stop.
- Say it. We're here!

393
00:22:05,933 --> 00:22:07,167
Say it!

394
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:13,200
What are you waiting for?

395
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,067
Say it, Jessica!

396
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:20,467
Coleen kicked me out,
Aunt Felma.

397
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,333
And she hurt me.

398
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:32,033
Hello, Didang, please
check on Coleen, okay?

399
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:33,100
She's still crying.

400
00:22:33,233 --> 00:22:35,833
Sure, I'll go up
after I finish the laundry.

401
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:38,500
And please look
after Dad too, okay?

402
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:39,733
Okay, Didang.

403
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:40,900
Jeff,

404
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:42,367
I'll go with you.

405
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:45,433
Dad, it's fine.
I'll take care of Andrea.

406
00:22:45,567 --> 00:22:47,067
Son, come on.
Let me go with you.

407
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:51,033
Your sister needs support
from her family.

408
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:54,100
She needs us, son.

409
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,600
Alright, Dad.

410
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:01,500
Maybe this is your chance
to reconcile with Andrea.

411
00:23:01,633 --> 00:23:03,567
Okay, son.
I'll just get changed.

412
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,933
- Wait for me.
- I'll wait for you here.

413
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,300
See that?

414
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:12,900
You're so shameless.

415
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:14,567
You have no right...

416
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,067
Hazel!

417
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:21,533
Stop it!

418
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:25,567
Hazel, stop!

419
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,467
- Hello.
- Hello, guard.

420
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,433
- It's an emergency.
- We need you here upstairs.

421
00:23:34,567 --> 00:23:35,700
Okay, copy.

422
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:47,133
Andrea, we're here. Let's go.

423
00:23:47,267 --> 00:23:48,200
Okay.

424
00:23:48,333 --> 00:23:49,200
Come on.

425
00:23:51,633 --> 00:23:52,800
Let's go.

426
00:23:52,933 --> 00:23:54,100
Come on. Hurry.

427
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,167
Why did you bring
me here, Joel?

428
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:03,367
I thought we'd go
to your house in Calamba?

429
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,267
Jeffrey asked me
to bring you here.

430
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:07,067
So he can go to you.

431
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,633
What?

432
00:24:08,767 --> 00:24:10,900
Joel, some of the people who
invested through me

433
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:12,233
are from FMP.

434
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:13,767
Do you want them
to come after me?

435
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:15,600
Your mom talked to them.

436
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:18,367
How did Mom even find out?

437
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:24,900
One of those who called
you was Angge, from FMP.

438
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:28,033
She told me
they went to your mom.

439
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,933
Come on, let's go inside.

440
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:31,767
Wait.

441
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:33,833
You told Jeff?

442
00:24:34,867 --> 00:24:36,067
Why?

443
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,367
What are you all trying to do?

444
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,967
You want me to ask Mom
for help, is that it?

445
00:24:41,100 --> 00:24:42,300
You're in trouble.

446
00:24:42,433 --> 00:24:44,300
You need to stay
somewhere safe.

447
00:24:44,433 --> 00:24:45,700
So come on, let's go inside.

448
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:47,067
Hurry. Come on.

449
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,400
Andrea, please.

450
00:24:48,533 --> 00:24:51,167
You also need to talk to the
people who invested with you.

451
00:24:51,300 --> 00:24:52,133
Tell them.

452
00:24:52,267 --> 00:24:54,267
Explain that you're
Elvie's victim, too.

453
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,833
You need to clear your name,
Andrea. Let's go inside.

454
00:24:56,967 --> 00:24:59,100
Hurry. We'll talk later.
Come on.

455
00:24:59,233 --> 00:24:59,867
Let's go.

456
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,100
Come.

457
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,567
Come, let's go inside.

458
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:17,333
Why is there no guard?

459
00:25:21,533 --> 00:25:23,300
No, Joel. I don't want to.

460
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:25,267
Andrea.

461
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:28,400
I don't want
to ask Mom for help!

462
00:25:28,533 --> 00:25:30,167
I'll figure this out.

463
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:31,933
I'll handle it.

464
00:25:32,067 --> 00:25:34,500
Just get me out of here.

465
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:35,867
I don't want to stay here,
please. Take me anywhere.

466
00:25:36,033 --> 00:25:37,433
- Just not here.
- Andrea, come on.

467
00:25:37,567 --> 00:25:38,667
You're in trouble,

468
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:40,200
and you're still thinking
about your pride?

469
00:25:40,333 --> 00:25:41,567
Andrea!

470
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:54,800
Andrea!

471
00:25:58,333 --> 00:25:59,533
- Joel!
- Andrea?

472
00:25:59,667 --> 00:26:00,533
Andrea!

473
00:26:02,733 --> 00:26:04,200
Andrea!

474
00:26:05,133 --> 00:26:06,533
Jeff!

475
00:26:06,667 --> 00:26:08,433
Ma'am Felma,
there's a commotion downstairs!

476
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:11,100
The men with Ma'am
Andrea are fighting!

477
00:26:11,233 --> 00:26:12,000
- Andrea's down there?
- Yes, Ma'am.

478
00:26:12,133 --> 00:26:14,000
Hey, Felma! We're not done yet!

479
00:26:15,233 --> 00:26:16,133
Help!

480
00:26:16,267 --> 00:26:17,400
Sonny!

481
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:26,900
Dad!
